Requirements:

Python > v2.6 
Perl > 5.8.5

Options that control program usage include:

method <string> - string describing the method used to create comparative
models of proteins.

max_e_value <float> - positive floating point number describing maximum e-value
to use when deriving constraints for comparative modeling

date_cutoff <int> - number representing a date past which template PDBs are not
included for modeling. Useful in constructing benchmarks and excluding PDBs
published after a given date. As an example, 20060107 is January 7th, 2006. 

boinc_tag <string> - unique tag for running jobs on BOINC

prefix <string> - create directory structure under this path

native <string> - location of native PDB file
